{
  "texts": [
    "Most of the participants were female (68.3%), between 20 to 30 years old (53%), and single (69.2%).",
    "Using SmartPLS 4, this study used partial least squares structural equation modeling (PLS-SEM).",
    "The PLS-SEM method was used for the following reasons.",
    "The first advantage of this method is that it improves the consistency and accuracy of the results by incorporating measurement errors (Hair et al., 2011).",
    "Additionally, it is particularly useful when dealing with models that have multiple variables (Hair et al., 2013)."
  ]
}